\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_H::1><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\b\fs36 Importing Files\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\fs28 To bring in writing and research from other apps:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}In Scrivener\'92s binder, select the folder into which you wish to import the new files. Or, select the file under which you wish the files to be imported. (If you select a folder, the imported files will be placed inside it as the last items; if you select a file, imported files will be placed directly beneath it.)\
{\listtext	2.	}Go to 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f2\b File > Import > Files\'85
\f0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f1\fs28  in the main menu.\
{\listtext	3.	}In the file browser window that appears, select the files that you want to import.\
{\listtext	4.	}Click \'93Import\'94.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 All selected files and folders will be imported, including subdirectories, reproducing the file structure from the Finder in Scrivener\'92s binder. Imported text files will be converted so that they can be edited inside Scrivener. All other files will be copied into Scrivener.\

\itap1\trowd \taflags1 \trgaph108\trleft-108 \trbrdrt\brdrnil \trbrdrl\brdrnil \trbrdrt\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil 
\clvertalt \clcbpat4 \clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf5 \clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf5 \clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf5 \clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf5 \clpadl100 \clpadr100 \gaph\cellx8640
\pard\intbl\itap1\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf3 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\i\b Note:
\f0\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28  If you selected a folder or file contained inside the \'93Draft\'94 folder in step (1) above, you will only have the option of importing text file types from the file browser, because the \'93Draft\'94 folder only supports text files.\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Scrivener can import many different file types:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Word documents (.docx, .doc), rich text files (.rtf, .rtfd), plain text files (.txt), OpenOffice documents (.odt) and Final Draft files (.fdx) are imported as text that can be edited inside Scrivener.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\li1440\fi-1440\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u8259 
\f1 	}Note that we are unable to support the Apple Pages file format because Apple has not made the format public. To import documents from Pages, first export them from Pages as .docx files, and then import the .docx files into Scrivener.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Image, movie, sound and PDF files are copied into Scrivener and can be viewed in its editor.\
{\listtext	\'95	}All other files are copied into Scrivener and are displayed in the editor using macOS\'92s Quick Look viewer.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb300\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

